<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Surinam To Expand Parliamentary Exchanges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 26 (Xinhua) -- China's National People's
Congress (NPC) is keen on expanding parliamentary exchanges with
Surinam, Vice-Chairperson of the NPC Standing Committee Chen Muhua
said here today.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Desire Delano Bouterse, special envoy of
the president of the Republic of Surinam, Chen said that the NPC,
China's top legislature, attaches importance to promoting the
friendly relations between China and Surinam. She said that the
NPC wishes to expand friendly exchanges with the National Assembly
of Surinam.
</P>
<P>
Bouterse conveyed condolences on behalf of the Surinam
government and people on the passing away of senior Chinese leader
Deng Xiaoping, for which Chen expressed her gratitude.
</P>
<P>
Chen asked Bouterse to convey greetings from her and Qiao Shi,
chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, to the chairman and
vice-chairman of the National Assembly of Surinam.
</P>
<P>
She said that she was very impressed during her visit to
Surinam in July 1993.
</P>
<P>
Bouterse said that the Surinam government attaches importance
to strengthening and deepening the friendly and cooperative
relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that Sino-Surinamese relations, including the relations
between the parliaments of the two countries, will see further
growth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
