<HEADLINE> Bosnia Qualify for Semifinals of Dunhill Cup Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Bosnia-Herzegovina
qualified for the semifinals of the Dunhill Cup soccer
championship with a 2-0 victory over Indonesia in a Group B match
here Wednesday evening.
</P>
<P>
Bosnia remained unbeaten to stay on top of the group with seven
points to take on Malaysia, the runner-up from the Group A, in the
second semifinal on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia finished the preliminary round with four points and
their fate for a semifinal berth depends on the outcome of another
Group B match between Zimbabwe and Vietnam later tonight.
</P>
<P>
If Zimbabwe beats Vietnam, Indonesia will be ruled out of the
top four, and Zimbabwe will meet the Group A champion, China in
the first semififnal on Friday.
</P>
<P>
In the match this evening, both teams started with an equal
chance to qualify for the semifinals but the Bosnians had the edge
with accurate long range passes which confused the Indonesians.
</P>
<P>
Bosnian skipper Begic Senad was the pillar in the heart of
defence to keep the Indonesians at bay with his excellent reading
of the game and timely intervention.
</P>
<P>
Bosnia, who beat Vietnam 4-0 and played to a 2-2 draw against
Zimbabwe, got the break when Indonesian goalkeeper Hendro Kartiko
charged Muhareovic Dzelaludin in a one-to-one situation.
</P>
<P>
Malaysian referee Nik Ahmad Yaakub blew for the penalty and
also flashed the yellow card to Hendro. Bosnia's Pintul Sanin
converted the penalty in the 29th minute.
</P>
<P>
Bosnia added another goal before the interval through Hrnjic
Asim in the 43rd minute via a simple pass from Dzelaludin.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia applied pressure in the second-half but failed to
equalize the score.
</P>
<P>
Following is table standings of the inaugural Dunhill Cup
soccer tournament (tabulated under games played, won, drew, lost,
goals for, against and points):
</P>
<P>
Group A;
</P>
<P>
China  3 3 0 0  2  2 9
</P>
<P>
Malaysia 3 1 1 1  2  3 4
</P>
<P>
Finland  3 1 0 2  3  4 3
</P>
<P>
Singapore  3 0 1 2  1  4 1
</P>
<P>
Group B:
</P>
<P>
Bosnia-Herzegovina 3 2 1 0  2  2 7
</P>
<P>
Indonesia  3 1 1 1  1  2 4
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe 2 0 2 0  2  2 2
</P>
<P>
Vietnam  2 0 0 2  0  5 0
</P>
</TEXT>
