<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Stresses Importance of Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 26 (Xinhua) -- The year 1997 is of great
significance to China as the Chinese government is to resume the
exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong and the Communist Party of
China (CPC) is to hold its Fifth National Congress.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, obtaining a bumper grain harvest is closely related
to the whole situation of the country's reform, development and
stability.
</P>
<P>
These remarks were made by Vice-Premier Jiang Chunyun here at
today's closing of a national work conference on administrative
restructuring of rural credit agencies.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Jiang said that China has made notable
achievements in agriculture and the rural economy in recent
years. China achieved good grain harvests in 1995 and 1996
successively, while township- and village-based industries have
also maintained a favorable trend of development, he said.
</P>
<P>
In 1996 Chinese farmers had a per-capita net income of 1,900
yuan, up eight percent over the previous year, and in the same
year some seven million poverty-stricken people in rural areas
were able to have enough food and clothing, according to the
vice-premier.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, Jiang said, the country's agriculture and rural
economy are expected to maintain their overall development
momentum, making new contributions to the entire national economy
and social stability.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier said that in 1997 China plans to achieve the
same grain output as last year, while trying to produce a bit more.
</P>
<P>
This year the country's township- and village-based enterprises
are expected to develop at a moderately fast pace, while the
per-capita income of the farmers is expected to increase by around
five percent, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also noted that the government plans to help some 12 million
rural people shake off poverty this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
