<HEADLINE> NPC Deputies Vow to Carry Forward Deng's Behest (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Legislators having arrived in
Beijing to attend the annual session of the National People's
Congress (NPC), China's legislature, vowed today that they would
carry forward the behest of Deng Xiaoping, who passed away
last Wednesday in Beijing, and make the session a success.
</P>
<P>
The Fifth Session of the Eighth NPC will start on March 1, and
last more than two weeks. Most NPC deputies have arrived in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Fourteen deputies from Jiangsu province, who arrived in Beijing
this afternoon, gathered to honor the memory of Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Xu Yan, vice director of the province's commission of
foreign trade and economic cooperation, said Deng
Xiaoping devoted his entire life to his motherland and the
people he deeply loved.
</P>
<P>
"As NPC deputies, we must live up to the trust and
expectations of the people, and turn grief into strength to do
a good job of discussing state affairs," he said.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Hu Fuming, vice chairman of the provincial committee of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference of Jiangsu,
said that the current session is of great importance, which should
take Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics as its guideline.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Li Qiankuan, a director for the Changchun Film Studio,
said the best way to commemorate Comrade Xiaoping is to make
more and better films to encourage the people.
</P>
</TEXT>
