<HEADLINE> NPC Deputies Vow to Carry Forward Deng's Behest (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As soon as NPC deputies from south China's Hunan Province
arrived in Beijing, they turned on TV sets to watch the live
telecast of the memorial meeting for Deng Xiaoping. At night, they
were seen preparing motions for the coming NPC session.
</P>
<P>
In Miaogou Village in the Zaoyuan Township of northwest China's
Shaanxi Province, per capita annual income today stands at 5,000
yuan (about 620 US dollars), compared with a mere 40 yuan in the
late 1970s, said Wang Jiufu, an NPC deputy from the village.
"Without reform and opening-up policies initiated by Deng
Xiaoping, we farmers would never have lived such a good life," he
said.
</P>
<P>
said Zuo Mingzhong, a deputy from Guang'an County, Sichuan
Province, "The 4.2 million people in Guang'an County, Sichuan
Province, Comrade Deng Xiaoping's hometown, will carry forward the
behest of Deng Xiaoping and rally around the Communist Party of
China Central Committee with Comrade Jiang Zemin at the core to
build Guang'an into a more prosperous place."  
</P>
</TEXT>
