<HEADLINE> China's Army Team to Compete in HK's Rugby Tens Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 26 (Xinhua) -- A team from China's People's
Liberation Army (PLA) Sports Institute will compete for a second
consecutive year in Hong Kong's annual Carlsberg Rugby Tens
Tournament next month, organizers announced here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The participation at last year's 10-a-side event by the PLA
team from the Institute based in Guangzhou, South China, became
the main topic at the tournament.
</P>
<P>
Also to participate in this year's competition will be another
Chinese team, that from the Beijing-based China Agricultural
University.
</P>
<P>
This year's event, slated for March 18 and 19, has attracted a
field of 38, similar in scale to last year.
</P>
<P>
They were pooled into eight groups of four for the first-stage
competitions. Winners of the groups will enter the Cup
quarter-finals, runners-up of each group will compete in the Plate
quarter-finals and the third-placers of the groups are to compete
in the Bowl quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
Nikon Mana Magicians from Japan, U.S. Hogs RFC and Tokyo Gaijin
RFC won the Cup, Plate and Bowl events last year.
</P>
<P>
Mana Magicians came back this year in the name of FPD Guard
Force Magicians.
</P>
<P>
The games are to be played at the Hong Kong Football Club and
the Happy Valley grounds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
