<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Signs Law on 1997 Budget </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
Tuesday signed a law on the 1997 budget, Russian Prime Minister
Viktor Chernomyrdin announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister told the Itar-Tass news agency that the main
financial law of the country would be published soon.
</P>
<P>
The 1997 budget, approved earlier by both houses of the
parliament, the State Duma and the Federation Council, projects an
expenditure of 529.9 trillion rubles (96 billion U.S.dollars), 21
percent up from the 1996 budget figure, and a revenue of 434.4
trillion rubles (79.18 billion dollars), 25 percent higher than
1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
