<HEADLINE> CPPCC Session Receives 90 Proposals (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 26 (Xinhua) -- The Fifth Session of the
Eighth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) has received 90 proposals.
</P>
<P>
Economic development in the first year of the Ninth Five-Year
Plan period (1996-2000) and the realization of China's long-range
goals for the year 2010 remain the central issue for the members
of the CPPCC National Committee, officials of the CPPCC National
Committee analyzed.
</P>
<P>
They added that there is a distinct rise in the number of
proposals for cultural and socialist ethical progress.
</P>
<P>
A proposal on how to ensure the top quality of the Three Gorges
Dam project has been cited as the No.1 for the coming session. Zhu
Baifang, a senior engineer who has made surveys of the Dam area
for several times, said in the proposal that the Three Gorges
Project is the world's largest water conservancy and hydraulic
project, as well as a super big project on the Yangtze, China's
longest river.
</P>
<P>
As result, he noted, first-rate quality must be sought for the
project.
</P>
<P>
Zhu also set forth suggestions on how to enhance quality
supervision, improve the technological system of the project, and
optimize bidding techniques for the project.
</P>
<P>
The Proposals-Handling Subcommittee is expected to receive a
larger amount of proposals before March 7, the deadline for
submission of proposals, its official said.
</P>
</TEXT>
