<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, ASEAN Cooperation Emphasized at CAJCC Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 26 (Xinhua) -- China and the ASEAN developed
a new channel of cooperation by setting up the China-ASEAN Joint
Cooperation Committee (CAJCC) here today.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen said
during the opening of the committee meeting that the committee was
an important follow-up step to seal China's full dialogue
partnership with the Association of Southeast Asia Nations (ASEAN).
</P>
<P>
"The first meeting of CAJCC gives us a good opportunity to
compare notes and pool our wisdom," he said.
</P>
<P>
CAJCC is an umbrella committee charged with overseeing the
various facets of China-ASEAN relations, ranging from trade and
economic matters to science and technology, culture, information,
environment and social development.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN is comprised of seven countries: Brunei, Indonesia,
Malaysia, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that the committee would work in the spirit of
equality, mutual benefit and friendly cooperation and put forward
detailed proposals for deeper cooperation between China and ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
He said that developing a good-neighborly partnership of mutual
trust with ASEAN was an important component of China's foreign
policy. He said that China would continue to work actively and
effectively for the deepening of bilateral cooperation in all
fields.
</P>
<P>
He said that China-ASEAN cooperation held out even broader
prospects, based on the premise that the rise of China and ASEAN
members serves peace, stability and prosperity in Asia and the
world.
</P>
<P>
He noted that there was a great deal of common ground between
China and ASEAN. Both attached importance to maintaining regional
and global peace, stability and development, and were dedicated to
this end.
</P>
<P>
He said that China and ASEAN were each committed to economic
development, regarding maintaining domestic stability and running
a successful economy as the central tasks.
</P>
<P>
Both need to safeguard the legitimate rights and interests of
the developing countries and work together to promote regional and
global cooperation on the basis of equality and mutual benefit, he
said.
</P>
<P>
He said that China and ASEAN both adhere to the principle of
non-interference in each other's internal affairs and stand for
closer dialogue and cooperation and peaceful settlement of
disputes between states.
</P>
<P>
"I am convinced that, based on these common positions, we are
fully capable of broadening the all-round cooperation between
China and ASEAN, and making its scope and depth more commensurate
with each other's needs and potentials of development," he said.
</P>
<P>
He told the first meeting of CAJCC that the Chinese people are
profoundly saddened by the death of Deng Xiaoping, an outstanding
leader and chief architect of China's reform, opening up and
modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
The great cause of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics that Deng initiated would continue to move
forward. The friendly relations and cooperation between China and
Asia and the world as a whole would grow stronger, he said.
</P>
<P>
In his speech delivered at the inauguration, Ajit Singh,
secretary-general of ASEAN, extended his condolences over the
death of Deng Xiaoping, and he attributed the improvement and
strengthening of China-ASEAN relations to Deng's leadership.
</P>
<P>
He said that "to ASEAN, relations with China are very
important," and that though there may be differences between the
ASEAN and China from time to time, as good neighbors, "we can
resolve them in a peaceful and friendly way, through consultations
and negotiations."
</P>
<P>
He noted that relations between China and the ASEAN countries
date back to ancient times and are firmly grounded, and bilateral
trade and economic ties have had remarkable growth in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Noting that ASEAN-China relations are "active and fruitful,"
Singh said that the CAJCC will be another important mechanism, as
it will oversee the various facets of ASEAN-China relations,
ranging from trade and economic matters to science and technology,
culture, information, environment and social development.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the frequent contacts, broadening
cooperation and growing goodwill will provide a firm basis for the
work of the CAJCC, which will give further impetus to the
cementing of closer and more meaningful ties between ASEAN and
China.
</P>
<P>
The first meeting of CAJCC runs through Friday. It is being
co-presided over by Chen Jian, assistant Foreign Minister of
China, and Abdul Majid Ahmad Khan, Director-General of the ASEAN
Department of Malaysian Foreign Ministry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
