<DOCNO> XIE19970227.0019 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPPCC Session Receives 90 Proposals (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Subcommittee for Handling Proposals of the National
Committee of the CPPCC has received 2,498 proposals since the
Fourth Session of the Eighth National Committee of the CPPCC, of
which 2,380 have been put on file for further deliberations. A
total of 1,620 members, or 77 percent of the total, have offered
their proposals.
</P>
<P>
The proposals cover issues on the sustained, rapid and healthy
development of the national economy, on promoting fundamental
changes in the economic structure and economic growth mode, on
consolidating the position of agriculture, on promoting ethical
progress and education and public health, on building up democracy
and the legal framework, and on the peaceful reunification of the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
Since that session, 161 government agencies including the CPC
Central Commission for Discipline Inspection, the Supreme People's
Court, the State Education Commission and the Ministry of
Broadcasting, Film and Television have been involved in the
handling of proposals.
</P>
<P>
By February 14, 2,334 proposals, or 98.1 percent of the total,
had been given an answer. In another analysis, problems covered by
1,937 proposals, or 83 percent of the total, have been settled or
are yet to be resolved. 
</P>
</TEXT>
