<HEADLINE> Norway Wins Nordic Combined </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Norway won the Nordic
Combined team event at the Nordic skiing world championships in
Trondheim, Norway on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Finland and Austria finished second and third respectively.
</P>
<P>
Halldor Skard, Bjarte Engen Vik, Knut Tore Apeland and Fred
Borre Lundberg won the ski jumping ahead of Finland and the Czech
Republic, despite a massive jump of 99.5 meters from Jan Matura.
</P>
<P>
That allowed the Norwegians to start the 4x5km cross-country
relay with a seven second advantage on the Finns and Halldor Skard
effectively killed off the contest by setting a terrific early
pace.
</P>
<P>
Finland recovered to overhaul the Austrians while defending
champions Japan, never in the hunt after a disappointing showing
in the ski jumping, finished ninth.
</P>
<P>
The Norwegians finished in 52 minutes 18 seconds for their
country's third gold medal in three days after the golden double
from Bjorn Daehlie. 
</P>
</TEXT>
