<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Industrial Facilities Quickly Improved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 26 (Xinhua) -- China has largely accelerated
its pace of upgrading and renovating its industrial facilities
over the past decade, with 26.1 percent of the manufacturing
equipment in large and medium-sized enterprises meeting the
international technical standard.
</P>
<P>
According to the newly-released results of a nationwide
industrial survey, the combined value of fixed assets in 1995
reached 4,789.66 billion yuan in enterprises that report annual
sales of no less than one million yuan, 6.7 times that in 1985.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, each employee's average proportion of fixed assets
equipment stood at 47,098 yuan, 4.4 times that of 1985.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, about 47.1 percent of the 3,200 kinds of major
industrial manufacturing equipment in enterprises above
township-level were imported from foreign counties. This figure
represented an increase of 28.9 percentage points over that of
1985.
</P>
<P>
Among the 1,180 types of major manufacturing equipment in the
country's large and medium-sized enterprises, some 26.1 percent
had met the international technical benchmark by the end of 1995,
up 13.2 percentage points from a decade earlier. 
</P>
</TEXT>
