<HEADLINE> HK Tall Ship Spectacular to Mark Start of Int'l Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 26 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Victoria
Harbor will be transformed into a spectacle at a late March Friday
with more than 30 sailing vessels taking part in a parade to mark
the start of the "Sail Osaka '97", organizers said here on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Osaka race will be the first international tall ship race
ever held in the Northern Pacific.
</P>
<P>
The race, organized by the city of Osaka and assisted by the
International Sail Training Associations, will attract some 50
vessels from 18 countries and regions, such as Argentina,
Australia, Columbia, France, Indonesia and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The race is also a festival of sail promoting friendship among
the young participants and the citizens of the ports involved --
Hong Kong, Okinawa, Kagoshima and Osaka.
</P>
<P>
As Hong Kong is the starting port, the Urban Council and the
Marine Department, assisted by the Hong Kong Tourist Association,
play host by jointly staging the "Hong Kong Tall Ship
Spectacular". The carnival will include such events as
exhibitions and on-shore water sports demonstrations.
</P>
<P>
The participating vessels will sail northeastward to Okinawa on
the first race. A cruise-in-company, which is a non-race voyage
between Okinawa and Kagoshima, is to follow and the second race
will start from Kagoshima and finish at Osaka by the end of April.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong will be represented by its only ocean-going tall ship
 named "Ji Fung", a 132-foot sailing ship of Hong Kong Outward
Bound School. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970227.0030 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Issue One Billion Yuan in Bonds for Three Gorges Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 26 (Xinhua) -- China is ready to float one
billion yuan (about 121 million US dollars) in corporate bonds to
increase funding for the Three Gorges Project, with public
issuance scheduled to start on February 28.
</P>
<P>
China Yangtze Three Gorges Project Development Corporation
(CTGPC), which is both the issuer and the dam project proprietor,
said the bonds will be sold at their face value -- 100 yuan, 1,000
yuan and 10,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The bonds, rated AAA-, the second-highest rating possible, are
for three years with an annual interest rate of 11 percent, which
will not fluctuate in accordance with inflation.
</P>
<P>
Interest calculation will start from the day of issuance and
end upon expiration of the three-year term, when capital will be
repaid together with interest.
</P>
<P>
A team of underwriters, with Shanghai-based Shenyin &AMP; Wanguo
Securities Co. Ltd. as the lead sales agent and Citic Securities
Co. as the subordinate, has contracted to be the wholesaler. The
signing ceremony was held today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time the CTGPC will float domestic bonds,
said Lu Youmei, president of the corporation, at the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
"CTGPC will continue to issue bonds in the future, in
accordance with the project's need for funds and the market
situation," he said.
</P>
<P>
The bonds will be issued in bills and made available for
purchase to all urban and rural residents in China, enterprises,
government agencies and financial institutions. They can
voluntarily buy the bonds from underwriting team's approved
outlets in Beijing, Shanghai, Shenzhen, Wuhan, Yichang and other
parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
Buyers can transfer the bonds to others or use them as
mortgages.
</P>
<P>
After the completion of the issuance and upon approval, the
bonds will be listed for trading on the Shanghai Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
The bonds have full support from the Three Gorges Fund which
provides an irrevocable guarantee. The fund is composed of profits
from the Gezhouba Hydroelectric Power Station downstream from the
Three Gorges and revenue from minor extra charges on electricity
imposed in most parts of China.
</P>
<P>
The enormous power generating capacity of the future
hydroelectric power station to emerge at the dam site promises
considerable gains for potential investors, Lu said.
</P>
<P>
The station will have a generating capacity of 84.7 billion
kilowatt hours (kwh) a year, or one tenth of China's total power
supply by the project's completion in 2009.
</P>
<P>
Income from bonds to be issued will be used to offset a
shortfall of investment to the dam project left over from 1996.
</P>
<P>
Total spending on the Three Gorges Project was 8.2 billion yuan
last year, with 4.2 billion and three billion yuan coming
respectively from the Three Gorges Fund and State Development Bank
loans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970227.0031 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Chunyun on Reform of Rural Credit Agencies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Jiang Chunyun has
called on concerned departments to be fully aware of the important
status and role of rural credit agencies in the development of
agriculture and the rural economy as a whole.
</P>
<P>
He urged creative reform of the structure of rural credit
agencies so as to better serve farmers and the agricultural sector.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks here today at the closing of a three-day
national work conference on administrative restructuring of rural
credit agencies.
</P>
<P>
Jiang told the meeting that the government is not able to make
all the investment needed in the agricultural sector, as the
country has a large population and an underdeveloped
economy. Therefore, the banking industry should play its full role
in assisting the agricultural sector.
</P>
<P>
Credit agencies play a decisive role in the rural banking
sector, he noted.
</P>
<P>
According to official figures, China has over 50,000 rural
credit agencies, with a total staff of over 600,000 and total
assets of 1,400 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year rural credit agencies had 879.4 billion
yuan as the remaining sum of deposits and 629 billion yuan in
outstanding loans, while 80 percent of loans borrowed by rural
households and 70 percent of those borrowed by township- and
village-based industries came from these agencies.
</P>
<P>
Referring to administrative restructuring, Jiang insisted that
the reform must adhere to the principle of the cooperative system.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the ownership of rural credit agencies belongs
to the shareholders, and the head of an agency must be appointed
through democratic election by the members, while all major issues
related to the agencies must be decided by the members' congress
or the board of directors.
</P>
<P>
At least 50 percent of the loans issued by the agencies must go
to their members, he said.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier asked all rural credit agencies to reinforce
their management and improve the performance, noting that the
administrative restructuring of rural credit agencies and building
a rural cooperative banking system are a pioneering issue,
directly related to agricultural development, the well-being of
farmers and the prosperity of the countryside.
</P>
<P>
Jiang asked governments at various levels to strengthen their
leadership over the issue, and he asked the People's Bank of
China, the central bank, to reinforce its supervision and
administration of rural credit agencies and to support their
development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
