<HEADLINE> People of Central Party and Government Departments Commemorate Deng </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Following the funeral meeting
for Deng Xiaoping yesterday, departments under the Communist Party
of China (CPC) Central Committee and the central government have
held various activities to commemorate Deng.
</P>
<P>
People with the departments studied President Jiang Zemin's
eulogy on Deng Xiaoping, saying that they would cherish the memory
of Deng's merits and push forward China's socialist cause under
the leadership of the CPC Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at
the core.
</P>
<P>
The eulogy summarized Deng Xiaoping's outstanding deeds and
great bearing in his long revolutionary life, expounded the
precious wealth Deng left to the Chinese people, and proclaimed
that the people will continue to unswervingly carry on the
socialist undertakings, they said.
</P>
<P>
They agreed they would follow Deng's great thinking of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics and turn sorrow into
strength to create an even more beautiful, powerful and prosperous
China.
</P>
<P>
Almost all the departments, scores of them all together, have
held forums and picture exhibitions to commemorate Deng, and many
people wrote memorial articles.  
</P>
