<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Further Develop Gold Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 26 (Xinhua) -- China plans to turn out 100
tons of gold this year and earn 800 million yuan in profits from
this sector, according to an ongoing national gold work conference
here.
</P>
<P>
More efforts will be made to use advanced technology, cut down
production costs and strengthen management, in a bid to give an
impetus to the industry's sustained, speedy and healthy
development.
</P>
<P>
The industry will invest 1.6 billion yuan in fixed assets this
year, one billion yuan of which will be used for basic
construction; the other 600 million yuan will be used for
technological improvements. Thus, China's annual gold production
capacity is expected to be raised by 7.25 tons.
</P>
<P>
And 400 million yuan more will be injected into prospecting
this year, which is expected to add 150 tons of gold reserves.
</P>
<P>
China's gold production last year reached 120.6 tons, up nearly
12 percent over the previous year and 6.1 times the 1978 figure.
</P>
<P>
China aims to raise its annual gold production to 150 tons by
the turn of the century.
</P>
<P>
The industry has found it profitable to cooperate with foreign
partners in developing low-grade gold ore resources and in
risk-taking geological prospecting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
