<HEADLINE> Ethiopian, South African Chambers of Commerce </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, February 26 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian chamber of
commerce and the Johannesburg chamber of commerce today signed an
agreement providing for the enhancement of the liaison and
cooperation between the respective organizations in the field of
export, investment, business information and other commerce
oriented activities.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by Woubishet Workalemahu, President
of the Ethiopian and Addis Ababa chambers of commerce, and
Letitia Schutte, mission leader of the South African business
delegation at the Imperial Hotel here.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, the two chambers of commerce
should recommend to their respective commercial authorities all
such measures as in the opinion of the would be beneficial and
helpful to increase trade and economic cooperation between the
two organizations.
</P>
<P>
They will also take steps as may be necessary and feasible to
promote trade and economic cooperation between the two
organizations and notify and help each other where possible in
the holding of trade exhibitions or fairs for the promotion of
products of the two organizations.
</P>
<P>
The agreement would also enable the two chambers of commerce
exchange trade and market information and disseminate to the
businessmen of the two organizations information on the goods and
services respectively available, whenever possible.
</P>
<P>
The agreement will be in effect for a period of three years as
of the date of signature and will be extended if the two
organizations so approve prior to the termination. 
</P>
</TEXT>
