<HEADLINE> Zhuhai Holds Photo Show to Mourn Deng's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of locals in this
prosperous south China city flocked to a display of photographs in
commemoration of Deng Xiaoping, China's former senior leader who
died at the age of 93 a week ago.
</P>
<P>
The show, entitled "Comrade Deng Xiaoping in Zhuhai," displays
63 photos which illustrate Deng's two visits to this special
economic zone in Guangdong Province in 1984 and in 1992.
</P>
<P>
During his inspections, Deng affirmed the economic reform
achievements made by the local government, which had greatly
encouraged the local people to work harder and more efficiently.
</P>
<P>
The photos show Deng meeting with local government officials,
giving important speeches, visiting enterprises and staying with
ordinary citizens.
</P>
<P>
The show, organized by the municipal committee of the Communist
Party of China and the city government, opened on Tuesday, the
same day that a huge memorial meeting was held in Beijing's Great
Hall of the People to mourn for Deng. 
</P>
