<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Holds Seminar On Taiwan Uprising </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 26 (Xinhua) -- A seminar to mark the 50th
anniversary of the Taiwan "February 28 Uprising" was held here
today.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) and chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), attended the
seminar.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Qian Qichen, who is also a member of the Political
Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, delivered a speech at the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
He said, "At this moment we deeply cherish the memory of
Comrade Deng Xiaoping, who made a great contribution to carrying
forward the country's peaceful reunification process by putting
forward the 'one country, two systems' proposition."
</P>
<P>
"We will further adhere to the `one country, two systems'
principle under the leadership of the CPC Central Committee with
Comrade Jian Zemin at its core to make new contributions to the
reunification drive," he said.
</P>
<P>
Expressing his appreciation for the Taiwan people's patriotic
spirit in the movement for democracy half a century ago, he
pointed out that history has again proved that the fate of the
Taiwan compatriots is closely related to that of the Chinese
nation as a whole.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized that, as a patriotic democratic movement
demanding freedom and opposing the tyrannical Kuomintang, the
uprising was by no means an "exclusive" or "Taiwan independence"
movement as some people who harbor the vicious ambition of
splitting the island from China have alleged.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Chinese government always respects the demand
of the Taiwan compatriots, which was illustrated by the speech
made by President Jiang Zemin in 1995, and in a series of
government policies, regulations and measures governing the
protection of the legal rights and interests of the Taiwan
compatriots.
</P>
<P>
Finally he pointed out that the year 1997 marks a historic
turning point in China's history. With the resumption of the
exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong and Macao, the
reunification of Taiwan with the mainland has become a more urgent
mission for the whole Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
The seminar, attended by about 400 people, was organized by the
Taiwan Affairs Office of the State Council, the Association for
Relations Across the Taiwan Straits and the All-China Federation
of Taiwan Compatriots. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
