<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Israeli President Ezer Weizman
has expressed his conviction that the Middle East peace process
was still on track despite rows between Israel and Palestine over
construction of new settlements in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference after meeting British Prime
Minister John Major this afternoon, Weizman said that he was still
"very optimistic" about the future of the Middle East peace
process despite some "ups and downs you have today."
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Israeli plans to build 6,500 homes for
Jews in Arab East Jerusalem were expected to trigger new violence
in the area.
</P>
