have achieved in the past 20 years. For the first 30 years after
the establishment of the state of Israel, we were at each other's
throats."
</P>
<P>
The Israeli president, who arrived here Tuesday for his first
official visit to Britain, said, "I hope that in the foreseeable
future -- whether it is five years, three years, two years -- we
will have peace with all the Arab nations and sail merrily into
the 21st century."
</P>
<P>
On the same occasion, British Prime Minister Major said, "What
we have tried to do is act as a facilitator. I don't think it is
our job to add to the difficulties and it is our job to add to the
solutions." 
