<HEADLINE> Israeli Forces Bombard South Lebanese Village </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Israeli forces bombarded this
afternoon villages near the frontier of the so-called "security
zone" in south Lebanon in retaliation for a guerrilla attack
on an Israeli convoy in the buffer enclave.
</P>
<P>
Security sources said that some 10 artillery shells fell
onto the village of Baraashit, Bint Jebeil, at 2:30 p.m. (1230
GMT), slightly wounding a 45-year-old woman.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli forces also bombarded Iglim Al-Toffah, a mountainous
area some 60 kilometers southeast of Beirut, which is often
used by Lebanese guerrillas as a springboard to launch attacks
on the Israeli-occupied border strip.
</P>
<P>
The Israelis fired 155mm heavy artilleries at Jebal Rafih
and the vicinities of Sujoud, Rihan and Beit Yahoun, the security
sources said.
</P>
<P>
Guerrillas of the pro-Iranian Hezbollah, or Party of God,
attacked this morning an Israeli convoy near an Israeli
position at Beit Yahoun, Beit Jebeil, without causing
casualties.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued in the Lebanese capital of Beirut,
the Islamic Resistance, the military wing of Hezbollah,
announced that its fighters launched the attack at 9:00 a.m.
(0700 GMT).
</P>
<P>
The Israeli occupation forces started the bombardment in the
morning following the guerrilla operation, and several shells
hit the place some 50 meters away from the public school
in Baraashit.
</P>
<P>
The sources, who asked for anonymity, noted that today's clash
did not go beyond a daily trade of fire on the last active
battlefront of the Arab-Israeli conflict.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, a top official of Hezbollah
warned today that his party would possibly resume Katyusha
attacks on northern Israel if the Jewish state continues
aggressions agaisnt Lebanese civilians. 
</P>
