<HEADLINE> E. African States Meet on Labor Issues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Three east African countries,
Uganda, Tanzania and Kenya, today started their meeting here on
labor legislation and policies.
</P>
<P>
Opening the three-day conference, Ugandan Deputy Prime
Minister and Minister of Labor and Social Welfare Paul Orono
Etiang urged delegates to come up with strategies and action plan
to reactivate the East African Community which broke up in 1977.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the community days of common standards, common
industrial court, similar employment legislation and free
mobility of labor in the region, Etiang said this is the
fulfillment everybody is looking forward to.
</P>
<P>
