informal sector, the joint East African Cooperation secretariat
formed in 1996 and the structural adjustment programs running in
the three countries, which draw the sister nations' attention to
the need for harmonization.
</P>
<P>
Andrea Singh, International Labor Organization area office
director for east Africa, pointed out that east Africa has been
touched by winds of change in globalization of trade, production,
information and communication which have made it inevitable to
work beyond national boundaries.
</P>
<P>
In light of these global challenges, she said the revival of
East African Cooperation is extremely important. She gave special
significance to the subject of child labor, which she asked the
delegates to look into. 
