<P>
The street kids to be taken in will acquire income-generating
skills such as bricklaying and carpentry instead of receiving
food through donations.
</P>
<P>
At the signing ceremony French Charge d'Affairs Renaud Guibert
said the HIV/AIDS pandemic has made thousands of Zambian children
become orphans and that such a project will enable these orphans
to become self sustaining.
</P>
<P>
The phase one of the center needs 330,000 Dollars and the
French government has provided 320,000 Dollars while the other
10,000 Dollars will come from non-governmental organizations.
</P>
<P>
The French diplomat expressed his hope that many
non-governmental organizations will be involved in the project.
</P>
<P>
About 200 street kids will be trained once the first phase of
the center became operational. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
