<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng Praised by Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan Delegates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Deputies to China's national
legislature and members of its top advisory body from Hong Kong,
Macao and Taiwan have expressed their heartfelt condolences for
Deng Xiaoping and asserted their confidence in China's
reunification.
</P>
<P>
Deputies to the Eighth National People's Congress (NPC) and
members of the Eighth National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) from the three regions
have gathered in Beijing to attend the fifth session of the NPC
and the fifth session of the CPPCC National Committee.
</P>
<P>
The principle of "One country, two systems" is a
crystallization of Mr. Deng Xiaoping's painstaking effort and
wisdom, said Ng Hong Mun, a Hong Kong deputy to the NPC.
</P>
<P>
Tsang Hin Chi, a member of the NPC Standing Committee and
chairman of Chinese Chamber of Commerce of Hong Kong, said that,
though Mr. Deng has passed away, his lofty moral qualities and
noble spirit will forever inspire him and other Hong Kong
compatriots to march forward.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong will return to the embrace of the motherland in more
than 100 days and all social circles in Hong Kong should unite as
one and make Hong Kong even more splendid, and this is the best
condolence for Mr. Deng," Tsang said.
</P>
<P>
Henry Hu Hung-lick, a member of the Standing Committee of the
CPPCC National Committee and a well-respected lawyer, recalled
that Deng Xiaoping talked of the Hong Kong issue when he was
hosting a dinner in honor of some Hong Kong guests on China's
National Day, October 1, 1979.
</P>
<P>
"Deng talked about finding a way to resolve the Hong Kong issue
that is welcome by Hong Kong people, and this demonstrated his
foresightedness," he said.
</P>
<P>
Realities over the past years have shown that Deng Xiaoping's
theory on the reunification of the motherland is entirely correct,
he said.
</P>
<P>
"Deng's 'one country, two systems" principle has created a
solid foundation for the reunification of the motherland, though
he was unable to live to see it," he said.
</P>
<P>
Tong Seng Chiu, President of General Association of Trade
Unions of Macao and an NPC deputy, said that compatriots in Macao
will always cherish the historic contributions made by Deng
Xiaoping and do all work well to accomplish Deng's unfulfilled
wish.
</P>
<P>
NPC deputies of Taiwan origin said that they admire Deng's
theory of "one country, two systems" and vowed to carry on Deng's
behest and redouble their efforts to work for the reunification of
the motherland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
