<HEADLINE> France Urges Investigation of Reported Genocide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, February 27 (Xinhua) -- France today called for an
international investigation into the reported genocide in the
rebel-controlled eastern region of Zaire, where half a million
Rwandan Hutu refugees were reported missing.
</P>
<P>
French Foreign Ministry spokesman Jacques Rummelhardt said that
the report, given by a Western witness in eastern Zaire and
published in Belgium earlier this week, "seems reliable."
</P>
<P>
The testimony on the massacres in eastern Zaire and the
discovery of mass graves there "seems reliable and has aroused a
very strong feeling," said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
"If the facts reported in the localities cited in this
testimony were effectively proved, it would be necessary to check
if these acts were generalized in the whole of Zaire and conducted
with a deliberate will," he added.
</P>
<P>
He said that the consequences to be drawn from the genocide
would be "evidently very grave" and that "only an international
inquiry with all the guarantee of objectivity could allow one to
establish truth in an inescapable way." 
</P>
</TEXT>
