<HEADLINE> Deng's Memory Cherished by CPPCC National Committee Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 27 (Xinhua) -- With profound grief over the
loss of Deng Xiaoping, members of China's top advisory body have
come to attend the annual session of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) today.
</P>
<P>
But this time, when they stepped into the imposing Great Hall
of the People, they cherished all the more the memory of Deng
Xiaoping, the late venerable Chinese leader who was reputed as the
founder of CPPCC's work in the new historical period.
</P>
<P>
Many members, who had participated in the Fifth National
Committee of the CPPCC, could not helping recalling the First
Session of the Fifth CPPCC National Committee held in the spring
of 1978, at which Deng Xiaoping was elected chairman of the Fifth
National Committee. And a new historical period for the
development of the political consultative cause has since been
ushered in.
</P>
<P>
Fang Rongxin, member of the Standing Committee of the Eighth
CPPCC National Committee and vice-chairman of the Chinese Peasants
and workers Democratic Party, noted that Deng Xiaoping led the
work of the CPPCC quickly back onto the correct track after a
decade of turmoil and wrote a new chapter for the cause of the
CPPCC.
</P>
<P>
Fang, also a a deputy secretary-general of the Fifth CPPCC
National Committee, added that Deng laid the foundation and
chartered the correct orientation for the CPPCC work.
</P>
<P>
The 75-year-old Wang Fu, a CPPCC National Committee member from
the educational circle, said with tears swelling in his eyes, that
he first met Deng at the first session of the Fifth CPPCC National
Committee. Deng was good at bringing their initiative into play,
and filled him with political enthusiasm, he said, adding that he
had subsequently set forth more than 20 proposals every year.
</P>
<P>
Ma Shigong, a CPPCC National Committee member donned in a
Moslem white hat, pledged to study Deng's theory of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics assiduously, and took an
active part in discussion on government affairs and suggested ways
and means. Meanwhile, he said, he will work hard to uphold
national unity and promote the unity of the motherland."
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong member Annie Wu Suk-ching said she cherished deeply
the memory of Deng Xiaoping at the eve of the realization of his
framework of "one country, two systems".
</P>
<P>
She said she will work hard to perform her duties well, so as
to contribute to China's economic development and opening-up
drive, as well as to Hong Kong's smooth return to the embrace of
the motherland as well as its prosperity and stability.  
</P>
</TEXT>
