<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 27 (Xinhua) -- A new format has been taken
for the 28th Viceroy Cup soccer tournament, Hong Kong's most
prestigious football tournament which kicks off on March 16,
organizers announced here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
For the first time in the event's history, a lower division
team will compete against the powerful First Division sides. And,
four days after the final set for April 6, the newly crowned
Viceroy Cup champions will face the Chinese professional team of
Apollo Guangzhou in the inaugural Viceroy Challenge Cup.
</P>
<P>
Champions Instant-Dict will try for the Viceroy Cup and a berth
in the Viceroy Challenge Cup.
</P>
<P>
Other First Division teams in the largest knock-out competition
are seven-times winners South China, and Golden, Sing Tao, Happy
Valley, Uhlsport-Rangers and Eastern.
</P>
<P>
Top amateur side the Hong Kong Football Club will be the only
one from the Second Division.
</P>
<P>
The total purse for this year's tournament has been increased
to 668,000 HK dollars (85,600 U.S. dollars), organizers
said. 
