<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australia reaps Record Grape Harvest In 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Australia's grape production
topped the one million ton mark for the first time in 1996 and the
successful harvest pushed wine exports to a record level.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Bureau of Statistics said today that the grape
production for all purposes reached 1,106,167 tons, compared with
the previous record of 987,142 tons set in 1992.
</P>
<P>
The total area under grapevine was a record 77,681 hectares.
</P>
<P>
A record 883,318 tons of fresh grapes were crushed for the 1996
vintage by wine makers, according to the publication.
</P>
<P>
Wine makers produced a record of 620.1 million liters, a 14
percent increase over 1994.
</P>
<P>
Stocks of Australian wine rose 22 percent and Australia
exported a record 129.5 million liters in fiscal 1996 valued at
470.7 million Australian dollars (362.44 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Despite the record wine production, there was also reportedly a
record set for imports with 20.3 million liters coming into the
country last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
