<HEADLINE> ADB Provides Loan for Vietnam's Water Supply Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, February 27 (Xinhua) -- The Manila-based Asian
Development Bank today approved a 69-million-U.S.-dollar loan to
Vietnam for a water supply and sanitation project.
</P>
<P>
The project will help more than a million Vietnamese, mainly in
low and middle-income groups, and businesses and industries in
seven provincial towns get cleaner and more plentiful water.
</P>
<P>
Currently, less than half of Vietnam's urban population receive
piped water, much of which is of poor quality. Water-borne
diseases cause up to a third of all deaths and an even higher rate
of infant mortality.
</P>
<P>
While improving urban environment and health, the project will
also design an environmental education program to increase public
awareness of the need for better hygiene and sanitation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
