<HEADLINE> SSA Company Makes Successful Start In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 27 (Xinhua) -- The System Software Associates
Company (SSA) from the US claims to have made a splendid start in
China this year by winning eight major Chinese companies'
agreements to buy its business management software during its
first fiscal year, through January.
</P>
<P>
The eight companies include the Shenzhen-based Konka Electronic
Group, a Chinese color TV giant, and the Qilu Petrochemical
Company in East China's Shandong Province. SSA's BPCS
client/server is designed to help companies achieve coordinated
management of supply, production and marketing.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Xu, manager of the marketing department, attributed the
company's success to its efforts in creating a market for business
management software at a time when Chinese companies are trying to
adapt to the needs of the new market economy.
</P>
<P>
Another secret of SSA's success in China is that SSA (China)
Co., Ltd, has all Chinese nationals at managerial level, Zhang
said, adding that this is also one area where SSA is different
from other foreign companies in China.
</P>
<P>
SSA (China) oversees business on the Chinese mainland, and in
Taiwan and Hong Kong. Last year SSA moved its Asia and Pacific
headquarters to Beijing, further highlighting its awareness of the
importance of China. 
</P>
