<HEADLINE> First Portugal-Financed Venture Inaugurated in Liaoning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Construction of Liaoyang
Efacec Electrical Equipment Co. (LEEEC), a Sino-Portuguese joint
venture, was completed Wednesday in the city of Liaoyang in
northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
LEEEC is the only Sino-Portuguese business in the province, and
also one of Portugal's most highly-financed ventures in China.
</P>
<P>
Visiting Portuguese President Joroe Sampaio attended a
ribbon-cutting ceremony for the venture Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
LEEEC is a joint venture between Liaoyang Transformers Factory,
a state-owned enterprise in central Liaoning, and Efacec of
Portugal, which is a comprehensive electrical and industrial
equipment conglomerate with advanced technology and management
expertise. The establishment of the joint venture, involving a
total investment of 22.6 million U.S. dollars, was first announced
in October 1994.
</P>
<P>
In addition to building closed workshops and an office building
of multiple uses, and rebuilding existing workshops, the new
company has also imported 331 sets of world-class transformer
manufacturing equipment from Portugal and Germany.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture will adopt the modern management methods used
by the Portuguese company and will produce various kinds of
transformers in line with international standards.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture will formally go into production in July.
</P>
</TEXT>
