<HEADLINE> HK Toys Sell Well on International Fairs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Record numbers of Hong Kong
manufacturers have participated in pavilions organized by the Hong
Kong Trade Development Council (TDC) at major toy fairs in New
York, the United States, and Nuremberg, Germany.
</P>
<P>
According to a TDC spokesman, 51 companies in Hong Kong's
pavilion at the 94th American International Toy Fair from February
14 to 17 in New York came away with total orders worth 18.4
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
An 84-company Hong Kong delegation to the Nuremberg
International Toy Fair in early February did total business worth
24.2 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that at the two fairs, Hong Kong had the
biggest overseas contingent, reflecting manufacturers' eagerness
to position themselves for an anticipated market revival.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's total toy exports exceed 10 billion dollars per
year, with the United States as the top market, followed by Japan,
Britain, Germany, China, Canada, France, Italy and the
Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
Louis Ho, TDC's senior manager for trade promotion, said market
conditions are expected to be improved considerably in 1997.
</P>
<P>
He said the most impressive growth will probably be in selected
categories like electronic or educational playthings and toys that
inspire creativity.
</P>
<P>
He said Hong Kong, the world's largest toy exporter, is
expected to continue its success at Tokyo Toy Show '97 from March
19 to 23.  
</P>
</TEXT>
