<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Newspaper Commentary To Mark Taiwan's "February 28 Uprising" (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The commentary calls on the Chinese people to continue to
follow the basic principles of "peaceful reunification" and "one
country, two systems," and implement President Jiang Zemin's
eight-point proposal on the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
During the struggle against separatism and "Taiwan
independence," the lifestyles of the Taiwan compatriots and their
desire to be their own masters were fully understood and respected.
</P>
<P>
It calls on the people to "still pin high hope on the Taiwan
people," strive to encourage the promotion of the relations across
the straits and make preparations for the realization of the
peaceful reunification.
</P>
<P>
In total defiance of the desires of the compatriots on both
sides of the Taiwan Straits, the Taiwan authorities not only
continued their attempts to create in the international community
the concepts of "two Chinas" and "one China and one Taiwan," but
also tried to hinder the development of relations across the
straits.
</P>
<P>
Not long ago, in an effort to deny Taiwan's status as one of
China's provinces and further create conditions for separating,
the Taiwan authorities convened the so-called Conference on
National Development, during which participants claimed to change
the administrative organization of the Taiwan province, an act
that moves dangerously toward the "nullification of the province,"
the commentary says.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese people firmly oppose the separatist activities of
"two Chinas" and "one China and one Taiwan" launched by the Taiwan
authorities.
</P>
<P>
It points out that all the Chinese people, including the Taiwan
compatriots, have reached a consensus on Taiwan's legal status as
a province of China's administrative division, and the fact that
it is part of China.
</P>
<P>
All this cannot be changed by the separatist powers, including
the "Taiwan independence" activists, the commentary says.
</P>
<P>
If the Taiwan authorities act willfully against history and the
people, their actions will only be ignored by history and the
people.
</P>
<P>
On July 1 this year, China will resume its exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong. This will have a significant and
profound influence on national spirit and will push forward the
process of reunifying the motherland.
</P>
<P>
The compatriots should continue to work for the reunification.
</P>
<P>
On the 50th anniversary of the "February 28 Uprising," the
commentary says, we express full respect for the uprising's
patriotic and democratic spirit and deeply understand the desire
of the Taiwan compatriots to be master of their own affairs.
</P>
<P>
We, together with the Taiwan compatriots and overseas Chinese,
should hold high the banner of patriotism and act with one heart
and mind to make historic contributions to the reunification of
the motherland and the overall rejuvenation of the Chinese
nation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
