<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambique Police Smashed 100 Criminal Gangs Last </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Mozambique police demolished
100 criminal gangs in Maputo province last year. Of these, 88
were armed gangs of robbery, eight were arms and drugs smuggling
groups, while the others were engaged in counterfeiting bank
notes, animal rustling and household electric appliances
stealing.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed today by spokesman Armenio Panguene of the
police bureau of Maputo province, according to a Mozambique News
Agency report.
</P>
<P>
The police captured from these criminals 98 vehicles, 110
acoustics units and other appliances, gemstones, ivories and
223 cattle, as well as heroin and other drugs.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the police also destroyed 27 arms hideouts,
took over 1,098 weapons of various kinds, 369 mines and
handgrenades and large quantities of ammunitions.
</P>
<P>
According to Armenio Panguene, 3,829 criminals have been
prosecuted and punished. Among them, 364 are youngsters and 458
are female. 
</P>
</TEXT>
