<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-U.S. Cooperation in Designing Big Nuclear Power Station </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese and American
researchers have completed all conceptual designs for a one
million kilowatt pressed-water nuclear power plant, the first of
its kind in China.
</P>
<P>
According to Qian Juexin, Engineer-in-Chief with the Shanghai
Nuclear Engineering Research and Design Institute who is also
responsible for the plans, the design work was done by Qian's
institute, together with the Shanghai Nuclear Power Office, East
China Electric Power Design Institute and Westinghouse of the
United States.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese partners drafted plans for the nuclear island and
conventional island, while the U.S. was in charge of mapping out
the nuclear steam supply system.
</P>
<P>
Qian explained that the cooperation is aimed at making full use
of and effectively absorbing the world's advanced experience and
promoting widely-accepted commercial nuclear power stations which
will not only suit China's situations, but also require lower
production costs compared with similar nuclear stations elsewhere.
</P>
<P>
Judging from the finished conceptual designs, Qian said,
China's million-kilowatt pressed water nuclear power plant will
approach the current world advanced standards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
