<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, ASEAN Strengthens Dialogue Mechanisms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 27 (Xinhua) -- China and the Association of
Southeast Asia Nations (ASEAN) agreed to step up their dialogue
and cooperation by forming a general framework for discussions.
</P>
<P>
Five organizations will contribute to the overall ASEAN-China
dialogue, Chinese Assistant Foreign Minister Chen Jian and
Director-General of ASEAN Department of the Malaysian Foreign
Ministry Abdul Majid told a joint press conference here today.
</P>
<P>
Chen and Majid co-presided over the first meeting of the
newly-established ASEAN-China Joint Cooperation Committee (ACJCC)
that ended here today.
</P>
<P>
The five organizations are the ACJCC, ASEAN-China Senior
Officials Political Consultations, ASEAN-China Joint Committee on
Economic and Trade Cooperation, ASEAN-China Joint Committee on
Science and Technology and ASEAN Committee in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The ACJCC will act as the coordinator of all the ground-level
ASEAN-China dialogue participants.
</P>
<P>
Chen and Majid agreed that the first ACJCC meeting was a great
success.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also agreed that ASEAN and China had a strong
foundation of cooperation and were fully complementary in such
areas as natural resources, industrial and technological
organization.
</P>
<P>
Both sides said they would expand their cooperation in
functional areas such as the economy, trade, science and
technology, and tourism.
</P>
<P>
The meeting approved in principle three joint venture projects
in the fields of personnel exchange, a workshop on economic and
trade cooperation and an information exchange.
</P>
<P>
Also adopted were the Terms of Reference of the ACJCC and the
Rules of Procedure of the Joint Management Committee of
ASEAN-China Cooperation Fund.
</P>
<P>
Both sides pointed out that remarkable progress has been made
in the relations between China and ASEAN as well as between China
and individual ASEAN members.
</P>
<P>
The political dialogue is at a high level, and the mechanisms
for economic, trade, science and technology cooperation are
operating smoothly. The two sides have coordinated with and
supported each other in regional and international affairs and
maintained an encouraging momentum, according to a joint press
release from the ACJCC meeting.
</P>
<P>
The release said that the next ACJCC meeting is to be held in
18 months in Malaysia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
