<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ASEAN to Form Broadcasters Confederation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Broadcasters of the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) today agreed to set
up an ASEAN Broadcasters Confederation.
</P>
<P>
An agreement to the effect is contained in a declaration signed
today by the heads of delegations of four ASEAN countries at the
end of the First ASEAN Broadcasters Conference in Langkawi, a
tourist resort island in the north of Malaysia, according to
reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
The signatories are Brunei, the Philippines, Singapore and
Malaysia. Delegations from the other three ASEAN members --
Indonesia, Thailand and Vietnam -- also supported the declaration,
but they did not sign it as they have yet to set up their own
national broadcasters associations.
</P>
<P>
Under the declaration, a steering committee will be set up,
comprising the heads of delegations of the four broadcasters
associations.
</P>
<P>
The three-day conference also recommended the setting up of
four working groups to deal with training, exchange of personnel,
exchange of programs, research and development and censorship in
line with technological advancement and the rapid development of
the broadcasting industry in the ASEAN region.
</P>
<P>
Delegates from Myanmar also attended the conference.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
