<HEADLINE> More Shanghai Companies Involved In Property Management </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Some 1,540 companies in
Shanghai, China's leading industrial and commercial center, have
registered to manage flats and other housing with a combined floor
space of 81.89 million sq m.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials, the flats and other housing
account for 68.8 percent of the city's total.
</P>
<P>
Last year, city departments adopted a series of measures and
policies to standardize property management, including putting a
price ceiling on open-market housing, repair work, and management
costs or fees, and for the sale of government-subsidized flats.
</P>
<P>
The city has also established 1,527 special committees for the
profession. 
</P>
