<HEADLINE> East China Redoubles Efforts To Control Huaihe River Pollution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, February 27 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province
recently declared that enterprises in the Huaihe River valley must
meet government standards for the discharge of pollutants within a
certain time period.
</P>
<P>
"Factories that fail to do so will be shut down," said an
official with the provincial government.
</P>
<P>
The province has drafted a plan to control pollutants from
enterprises in the valley. Over 310 factories are included in the
plan.
</P>
<P>
The State Council has stipulated that all polluting factories
in the valley must meet the government-set discharge standards
before the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
Some cities in the valley are speeding up construction of
plants for waste water disposal, and a number of localities have
taken steps to cooperate and raise funds, in a bid to fulfill
their targets in pollution control.  
</P>
</TEXT>
