<HEADLINE> China Concerned About Jewish Settlement Issue: Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 27 (Xinhua) -- China is deeply concerned
about Israel's recent establishment of a Jewish settlement in east
Jerusalem, Foreign Ministry spokesman Tang Guoqiang said here
today.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has consistently held that the issue of
Jerusalem should be solved by parties involved through peaceful
negotiations based on relevant UN resolutions, Tang said at a
routine press conference.
</P>
<P>
"We are deeply concerned about the issue," he said, "and
believe that this will create obstacles for the ongoing peace
talks between Palestine and Israel, and thus be harmful for the
Middle East peace process."
</P>
<P>
China hopes that parties concerned will act with caution and
create a fine atmosphere for the promotion of peace talks in the
Middle East, the spokesman added.  
