<HEADLINE> Increased Taiwan Investment for Central China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan
Province is now home to more than 900 Taiwan-invested enterprises,
involving an agreed use of 500 million million U.S. dollars of
Taiwan funds.
</P>
<P>
Information from the provincial Taiwan Affairs office shows
that Henan approved 95 new Taiwan-financed businesses last year,
involving a total investment of 100 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Local officials explained reasons behind the investment inflow
from Taiwan. Over the past years, while different localities of
the province have made painstaking efforts to improve its
investment environment, the provincial authorities have worked out
"regulations for protection of investment of Taiwan compatriots"
which will become effective on April 1.
</P>
<P>
Relevant provincial departments have also worked diligently to
successfully manage and serve existing Taiwan-funded enterprises
and properly handle disputes concerning them.  
