<HEADLINE> More Henan People Find Jobs in Private Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Some 3.2 million people in
central China's Henan Province are now working in the province's
1.55 million industrial and commercial enterprises run by
individuals and 26,200 private businesses.
</P>
<P>
The former usually employ around three people each, while
private businesses are larger and often have eight or more
employees each.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials, self-employed industrial and
commercial households are mainly engaged in the fields of mining,
construction, transportation, shipping and storage, wholesale and
retail business, and catering.
</P>
<P>
Up to the end of last year self-employed industrial and
commercial households, with a total registered capital of 9.4
billion yuan, had generated a total of 11.66 billion yuan in
output value and had made a total of 49.69 billion yuan in income,
showing marked increases over the previous year's figures.
</P>
<P>
Out of the 26,200 private businesses, 13,900 enterprises are
engaged in manufacturing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
