<DOCNO> XIE19970227.0144 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Top Advisory Body Opens Annual Session (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Members of the CPPCC National Committee attending the current
session will hear and examine a work report of the Standing
Committee of the Eighth CPPCC National Committee. They will
also, in a non-voting capacity, attend the Fifth Session of
the Eighth National People's Congress due to open here on March
1.
</P>
<P>
Members will hear a report on the handling of proposals by
the National Committee's Motions Committee.
</P>
<P>
During the session, members will also hear and discuss
Premier Li Peng's government work report.
</P>
<P>
Ye Xuanping, a vice-chairman of the CPPCC National Committee,
delivered the work report on behalf of the Standing Committee of
the National Committee.
</P>
<P>
In his report, Ye talked about new achievements made by the
Chinese people in economic reform, implementation of the
opening-up policy and the modernization drive under the guidance
of Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics and under the leadership of the CPC Central
Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core.
</P>
<P>
In 1997 China will resume the exercise of sovereignty over Hong
Kong, an important step in China's peaceful reunification, and the
CPC will convene its 15th National Congress. Both events will attract
worldwide attention and are of far-reaching significance, Ye said.
</P>
<P>
In the past year, Ye said, the CPPCC National Committee has
achieved fruitful results in participating in the running of
political affairs, voicing the will of the people, promoting the
peaceful reunification of the motherland, expanding its
external relations and consolidating itself.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, Ye said, the CPPCC National Committee will broaden
areas for its participation in the running of state affairs. The
committee, he said, will put forward proposals and policy
suggestions on some major subjects concerning national economic
and social development, and cultural and socialist ethical
progress.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the CPPCC National Committee will also actively work
for China's resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong
Kong in line with the principles of "one country, two systems,"
"Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong" and a high degree of
autonomy by encouraging members from Hong Kong and
Macao to play a more prominent role in participation in the
running of state affairs.
</P>
<P>
The vice-chairman said the top advisory body will also
contribute to the long-term stability and prosperity of Hong Kong
and Macao and the smooth transition of Macao. Ye said the CPPCC
National Committee will continue to develop friendly relations
with Taiwan compatriots by implementing the eight-point proposal
on promoting a peaceful reunification of the motherland put
forward by president Jiang Zemin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
