<HEADLINE> Share Prices Decline Sharply on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined
sharply on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index lost 25.44 points to close at 2190.63 points
today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume shrank to 399.77 million, valued at
757.78 million Singapore dollars (about 533.65 million U.S.
dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances 354 to 60 while 191 other
counters remained steady.
</P>
<P>
IGB TSR was the most actively traded counter as it registered a
turnover of 38.09 million units. It was followed by MBF Holdings
which had 19.96 million of its shares traded. Insas Bhd was next
with 13.9 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Overseas Chinese Banking Corporation (OCBC) Foreign led the
gainers of the day as it rose by 40 cents to finish at 18.7
Singapore dollars. GE Life gained 30 cents to close at 25.3
dollars, while Gentings was 25 cents higher at 9.85 dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the City Development Ltd. Hotel Ltd. and the
City Development Warrant98 shared the top spot on the losers' list
as each of them declined by 50 cents to end at 4.1 and 11.6
Singapore dollars respectively. Creative 50, the Overseas Union
Bank (OUB) Foreign, and the Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign
fell by 40 cents each to close at 18.2, 11.1, and 27.3 Singapore
dollars respectively.  
</P>
