<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tasks for China's Top Advisory Body in 1997: Ye Xuanping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 27 (Xinhua) -- China's top advisory body will
consolidate and develop the patriotic united front, promote the
great unity and alliance under the objective of invigorating the
Chinese nation and reunifying the motherland.
</P>
<P>
This was cited as the top task for the body in 1997 by Ye
Xuanping, vice-chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), on the opening
meeting of the Fifth Session of the Eighth CPPCC National
Committee held here today.
</P>
<P>
Among other tasks, the advisory body will give full scope to
the role of various non-Communist parties, figures without any
party affiliation, people's organizations and representatives of
various ethnic groups and from all walks of life, and assist the
Communist Party and government to consolidate and develop social
and political stability.
</P>
<P>
In his work report of the Standing Committee of the Eighth
National Committee delivered at the meeting, Ye conscientiously
summarized the Standing Committee's work in the past year, defined
its working policies and arrangement in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he said, "the CPPCC National Committee will hold high
the banner of Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics in 1997, to further consolidate the common
political basis for unity and cooperation," said the vice-chairman.
</P>
<P>
Noting that Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics is the crystallization of the collect
wisdom of the whole party and the entire Chinese people, he
praised Deng as the founder of the people's political consultative
cause during the new historical period. Deng has set forth a
series of ideas with major guiding significance since he became
the chairman of the Fifth CPPCC National Committee, Ye recalled.
</P>
<P>
Ye went on to say that the National Committee will urge and
organize its members to study in a deep-going way Deng's theory
and the theses of the Party Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at
the core concerning the united front and the people's consultative
cause and the guidelines set forth at the previous CPC Central
Committee sessions, so as to further strengthen the common
political basis composed of various parties, organizationss and
representatives of various ethnic groups and from all social
strata.
</P>
<P>
Ye said the committee will mobilize and organize all the
members to perform their duties well by making more surveys and
contributing more proposals on the central issue of China's Ninth
Five-Year Plan (1996-2000) and long-range goals for the year 2010,
and the promotion of socialist ethical and cultural progress.
</P>
<P>
"The National Committee will select some major topics
concerning national economy and social development, organize
surveys and discussions in a well-planned way, and submit
prosposals or spe top reports to the central authorities," Ye
said.
</P>
<P>
Ye added that the committee will summarize its work since its
first annual session in 1993, and prepare for the election of the
next CPPCC National Committee.
</P>
<P>
The year of 1998 shall see the re-election of both the CPPCC
and the National People's Congress, the Chinese parliament.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970227.0153 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tasks for China's Top Advisory Body in 1997: Ye Xuanping (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The CPPCC National Committee will continue to promote the
standardized and systematic political consultation, democratic
supervision, and participation in government affairs, Ye said.
</P>
<P>
The committee encourages each member to set forth at least one
quality proposal with substantive contents, or one valuable piece
of information every year, and improve the organs that are
responsible for reporting public feelings and popular will, he
noted.
</P>
<P>
To assist the Party and the government to consolidate social
and political stability, Ye said, the committee will help the
government to implement its policies concerning ethnic groups and
religions, and promote economic and cultural development in ethic
minority inhabited regions.
</P>
<P>
The committee, in accordance with the policy of "one country,
two systems" and the principles of "Hong Kong people governing
Hong Kong" and "a high degree of autonomy", will actively support
and assist the central government to do a good job in Hong Kong's
return of the embrace of the motherland, Ye said.
</P>
<P>
To carry out President Jiang Zemin's eight-point proposal on
the peaceful reunification of the motherland, the committee will
work hard for the accomplishment of direct exchange of mail,
trade, air and shipping services, as well as other exchanges in
economic and cultural fields.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, Ye added, the committee will steadfastly oppose to
any attempts for "two Chinas", "one China, one Taiwan", and "the
Independence of Taiwan", while working to safeguard the legal
rights and interests of the returned overseas Chinese and their
relatives.
</P>
<P>
The CPPCC National Committee will, through more and broader
channels, develop friendly relations with the corresponding bodies
in the relevant countries and noted figures, and strive to
contribute its share to the creation of a peaceful and stable
international environment for China's modernization drive, the
vice-chairman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
