<HEADLINE> Ramos Urges Action Against Migrants Trafficking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel
Ramos today called on government agencies and all sectors of
society to take action to eradicate illegal trafficking of
migrants.
</P>
<P>
In a proclamation released today, Ramos declared 1997 as the
Anti-Migrant Trafficking Year and asked government departments to
adopt measures and allocate resources to fight against illegal
trafficking of migrant workers.
</P>
<P>
Overseas employment continues to be an alternative source of
income for more than 4 million overseas Filipino workers, Ramos
said.
</P>
<P>
He added that in pursuit of overseas work, job seekers continue
to be victimized by illegal traffickers whose victims include
women and children.
</P>
<P>
The proclamation is part of the Ramos administration's
sustained efforts to protect Filipino workers from exploitation
and onerous employment terms and conditions.
</P>
<P>
Total remittances to the country by overseas Filipino workers
increased by as much as 57 percent, from 2.21 billion U.S. dollars
for the first six months of 1995 to 3.47 billion dollars during
the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The remittances were estimated to have reached 7 billion
dollars by the end of 1996 as compared to 4.93 billion for the
whole of 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
