<HEADLINE> 17 Suspects Moved to Ratnapura Courts for Trial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Seventeen suspects in the
Nalanda Ellawala murder case were moved from the Mahara prison in
Colombo under heavy security this morning to the Ratnapura
Magistrate Courts to stand trial, police sources here said.
</P>
<P>
The sources said all measures had been taken to ensure the
safety of the suspects. All police stations on the road to
Ratnapura from Colombo had been alerted and armed guards placed at
strategic points in addition to mobile patrols.
</P>
<P>
Among the suspects are Ratnapura District MP Susantha
Punchinilame and former Mayor of Ratnapura Mahinda Ratnatilleke,
the two key suspects in the killing of District MP Ellawala on
February 11 when political violence flared up after the nomination
of candidates for local government elections.
</P>
<P>
The suspects reportedly arrived at the Ratnapura courts without
any incidents.  
