<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Funding for Three Gorges Project Guaranteed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Sufficient funding has been
arranged for the Three Gorges Project since it was launched in
1994, said a senior official involved with the project.
</P>
<P>
The Three Gorges Construction Fund and the State Development
Bank loans have provided a stable financial guarantee for the
project's construction and the resettlement program, Guo Shuyan,
deputy director of the State Council's Three Gorges Project
Construction Commission, told reporters in Beijing Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1996, investment in the project had reached 20.8
billion yuan, with 11.1 billion from the Three Gorges Construction
Fund, 8.9 billion from State Development Bank loans, and the
remaining 800 million from other resources.
</P>
<P>
"The appearance of the dam site and the reservoir area are
changing with each passing day," Guo said, adding that workers are
busy meeting the goal of damming the Yangtze the coming November,
he said.
</P>
<P>
The Three Gorges Project, the largest capital construction
project in China, involves a static investment of 90.09 billion
yuan on May 1993 prices.
</P>
<P>
However, taking into account the factors of inflation and loan
interests, dynamic investment in the project could reach 146.8
billion yuan in the year 2005 and 203.4 billion yuan by the time
the project is complete in 2009, said Lu Youmei, president of the
China Yangtze Three Gorges Project Development Corporation (CTGPC).
</P>
<P>
The project will mainly depend on domestic funding which is
composed of four parts, namely, the Three Gorges Construction
Fund, profits from the Gezhouba Power Plant, profits from the
Three Gorges Power Plant which will generate electricity beginning
in the year 2003, and State Development Bank loans.
</P>
<P>
The domestic fund will meet the majority of the project's
financial needs, but a funding shortage still exists, Lu said.
</P>
<P>
To cover the shortfall, the CTGPC, proprietor of the project,
will moderately use foreign export credits, commercial loans and
issue bonds both at home and abroad at a certain time.
</P>
<P>
The first batch of bonds, totalling one billion yuan, will be
floated domestically from February 28 to March 18.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 2005, ten generating units will produce
electricity, which will greatly increase the project's repayment
ability and give it a capital surplus.
</P>
<P>
Project spending this year is budgeted at 8.9 billion yuan
(about 1.1 billion US dollars), when the dam scheme will proceed
into its second phase of construction after the damming of
Yangtze. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
