<HEADLINE> 30 Rebels Killed in W. Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, February 27 (Xinhua) -- The Ugandan army killed more
than 30 rebels of the Allied Democratic Forces (ADF) in western
kasese District on Tuesday, local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
The New Vision quoted a government army officer from the
battle field as saying "We lost at least five."
</P>
<P>
"The Monitor" said the ADF rebels often creep in night
from their hideouts in small groups of four or five to steal
food.
</P>
<P>
Lillian Achan Oketch, Chairperson of the Kasese District Security
Committee and Resident District Councillor, said that there are
some 200 ADF rebels in Mahango and Kyarumba mountains in
Kasese District.
</P>
<P>
The ADF had some 1,000 members last November. Recent reports
indicated traces of their minor presence in western districts of
Bushenyi and Kabarole, since the Ugandan army uprooted their
hideouts in Rwenzori Mountain in Kasese District earlier last
January. 
</P>
