<HEADLINE> Finnish Telecom Firm Awarded Network Contract in Henan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Nokia, the leading Finnish
supplier of mobile telecommunications, sealed a deal with central
China's Henan Province to expand the digital mobile phone network
there.
</P>
<P>
The recent issue of China Electronics News said that Nokia
began to supply the province with its GSM (global service for
mobile communication) in the first quarter of 1997, in order to
expand the switching capacity and coverage of Henan's cellular
phone system.
</P>
<P>
The GSM contract, involving 75 million US dollars, was signed
by Henan's posts and telecommunications administration and Beijing
Nokia Mobile Telecom Ltd., a Sino-Nokia joint venture launched in
Beijing in April of 1995.
</P>
<P>
When the expansion project is completed, Henan will have a GSM
switching capacity to handle 500,000 handsets.
</P>
<P>
Henan initiated the digital mobile phone service in April of
1996, when Nokia helped it launch a province-wide GSM network.
</P>
</TEXT>
