<HEADLINE> Sixty Percent of Shanghai Stock Building Leased Out </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Sixty percent of the
floor-space of the newly-constructed Shanghai Stock Building has
been sold or leased out to local and overseas stock dealers,
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The building, with 30 floors including three basement levels,
costs 148 million US dollars and is scheduled to go into trial
operation by May 1.
</P>
<P>
In June, the Shanghai Stock Exchange is expected to occupy
eight floors, from the second to the ninth.
</P>
<P>
Although office space has been sold at an average of 2,700 US
dollars per sq m, so far the most expensive in this largest city
in China, many Chinese and foreign companies including those from
the United States and the Republic of Korea have purchased or
rented rooms there.  
