<HEADLINE> Vietnam Needs Investment in Oil and Gas Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Petrol Vietnam, Vietnam's
state-run oil company, estimated that Vietnam will need about six
billion U.S. dollars to develop its oil and gas industry from now
to the year 2000, the local media reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report said the estimated figure does not include 1.3
billion U.S. dollars to build the first oil refinery in Dung Quat
industrial zone of Quang Ngai province.
</P>
<P>
