<HEADLINE> Xiamen Launches Re-Employment Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, February 27 (Xinhua) -- This city in southeast China's
Fujian Province has launched a re-employment project aimed at
keeping the city's unemployment rate at under one percent.
</P>
<P>
The main guidelines of the project are to let the elderly
retire gradually, train middle-aged workers to help them find new
jobs and encourage young people to obtain jobs by themselves.
</P>
<P>
A group of labor markets is to be built, computer data banks
connected with labor resources will be hooked up among various
districts, and regulations will be drawn up to ensure the smooth
operation of these markets.
</P>
<P>
The city has decided to spend three years sponsoring 24 terms
of working-skill training classes, to train a total number of
nearly 20,000 people.
</P>
<P>
A special fund of 13 million yuan (about 1.5 million US
dollars) will be raised from government, society at large and
enterprises to provide financial guarantees for the re-employment
project. Meanwhile, a re-employment service center will be set
up. 
</P>
