<HEADLINE> Ye Xuanping on CPPCC Achievements In 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 27 (Xinhua) -- The Standing Committee of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC) has scored new achievements in various aspects
of work during the past year, a leading official of the CPPCC said
here today.
</P>
<P>
In his report on the Standing Committee's work to the opening
meeting of the Fifth Session of the Eighth CPPCC National
Committee, Ye Xuanping, vice-chairman of the CPPCC National
Committee, described the work of the top advisory body as ushering
in "a lively, vigorous, and encouraging state."
</P>
<P>
He said that in 1996, the Standing Committee of the CPPCC
National Committee had focused on serving the central tasks of the
Party and the government, and performed its duties with flying
colors.
</P>
<P>
"To help the implementation of the Ninth Five-Year Plan
(1996-2000) and the outlined long-term objectives for 2010,
various subcommittees under the Standing Committee last year
carried out a series of investigations and studies and filed a
total of 41 study reports and special proposals, which drew
great attention from the Party Central Committee, the State
Council, and other relevant departments," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he said, the Standing Committee in 1996 received a
total of 2,498 proposals, 2,380 of which were accepted, a marked
increase over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
"The proposals were made by 1,620 members of the CPPCC National
Committee, 77 percent of the total, and provided important
reference to the Party and the government institutions for
decision-making procedures," he added.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that the CPPCC conducted varied activities to
help promote the motherland's reunification in accordance with the
principles of peaceful reunification and "one country, two
systems."
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he added, "we have increased our ties with the
compatriots in Taiwan, Hong Kong, and Macao, and organized CPPCC
members from Hong Kong and Macao to visit the interior areas so as
to help acquaint themselves with the country's current situation
and its economic development and social progress."
</P>
<P>
The CPPCC also developed friendly relations with foreign
countries and international organizations extensively, and had
established links with 61 countries and 86 agencies under four
international organizations by the end of 1996.
</P>
<P>
"During the past year, the Standing Committee sent eight
delegations to 15 countries, while inviting six foreign
delegations to China," Ye noted.
</P>
<P>
He added that the Standing Committee also hosted a number of
commemorative activities on important occasions to promote
patriotism, and made painstaking efforts in building a
standardized system of political consultation.
</P>
<P>
While marked progress has been made, he acknowledged, the work
of political consultation, democratic supervision, and
participation in the government and political affairs still needs
to be strengthened and further improved.
</P>
<P>
"Overall, it is still necessary for us to further enhance the
democratic supervision, which is rather weak, and to explore into
further increasing the connections with various non-Communist
parties and the people's organizations," Vice-Chairman Ye Xuanping
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
