<HEADLINE> Krajicek, Washington Set to Play India Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Wimbledon champion Richard
Krajicek of the Netherland and runner-up American Malivai
Washington will take part in the Indian Open tennis tournament
scheduled on April 7-13 in Madras, organizers said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
World number eight Thomas Enqvist of Sweden and India's
Olympic bronze medalist Leander Paes will also appear in the
tournament.
</P>
<P>
Former Indian Davis Cup captain Vijay Amritraj said seven other
players from the world's top 20 would be in the 32-player draw.
</P>
