<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eastern China Province Opening Wider </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, February 27 (Xinhua) -- The governor of east China's
Shandong province, recently addressing the fifth session of the
eighth provincial people's congress, said that the province will
open wider to the outside world this year.
</P>
<P>
Governor Li Chunting said that his province will try to
increase foreign trade, especially processed goods and those with
high added value.
</P>
<P>
The export of machinery, electronics, and processed farm
products, and the import of key technology and equipment, will be
given more attention, he added.
</P>
<P>
The province also plans to encourage firms with good profits to
operate overseas. Foreign investment will be better controlled to
ensure that more funding goes into agriculture, basic industries,
and high-tech industries, said Li.
</P>
<P>
It will further improve its investment environment and provide
better services for foreign investors.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the province last year had foreign trade
worth 17.8 billion US dollars and used foreign funds worth 3.2
billion US dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
