<HEADLINE> China-US Copyright Cooperation for VCDs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, February 27 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen Xianke Group of
China, which signed a one-year copyright agreement last July with
the U.S.'s Warner Home Video, will put its video compact discs
(VCD) and laser discs (LD) of five American films on the domestic
market in mid-March.
</P>
<P>
Ye Huapeng, chairman of the board of Shenzhen Xianke, told
Xinhua that his company has produced 10,000 VCDs and 1,000 LDs of
the films, including "The Fugitive", "Rain Man," and "Outbreak."
</P>
<P>
Xianke, China's top compact disc producer, will soon introduce
another nine U.S. films. Warner will be paid a certain percentage
of sales of the discs, Ye said.
</P>
<P>
So far, a number of VCD and LD salesmen have ordered the five
films and say they believe that they will sell well, because they
were box-office hits in the United States.  
</P>
</TEXT>
