<HEADLINE> s d s 1051 China-CPPCC-Opening Annual Session of CPPCC National Committee Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 27 (Xinhua) -- The Fifth Session of the
Eighth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), China's top advisory body, opened
here this afternoon in the Great Hall of the People.
</P>
<P>
Attending today's opening meeting are 1,846 members.
</P>
<P>
During the 13.5-day session, some 2,000 members will hear and
discuss the work report of the Standing Committee of the CPPCC
National Committee and a report on the handling of proposals since
its last annual session.
</P>
<P>
Besides, in a non-voting capacity, they will hear and discuss a
government work report to be delivered by Premier Li Peng and
other important reports at the Fifth Session of the Eighth
National People's Congress (NPC).
</P>
<P>
After announcing the opening of the annual session, Li Ruihuan,
chairman of the CPPCC National Committee, proposed that all
present stand up in silent mourning for Deng Xiaoping, who passed
away last Wednesday in Beijing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
