<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Central China Coal Mines Report Sideline Production Profits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Sideline production has
turned coal mines in central China's Hunan Province from monstrous
money losers into money-makers.
</P>
<P>
According to information from the provincial coal
administration, last year state-owned coal mines above the county
level generated 1.5 billion yuan in output value and sideline
production, and earned a profit of 35 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Mine conditions had been very poor in much of the province and,
because of high production costs a great number of mines suffered
severe economic losses for quite a long time. Later the central
government decided to lift the price ceiling on coal in 1993.
</P>
<P>
With the help of local and central governments, different coal
mines have developed reform measures to make their workers more
enthusiastic and to encourage surplus workers to engage in
sideline production to reduce production costs, especially in view
of the fact that resources are shrinking.
</P>
<P>
Surplus workers from coal mines have turned their hand to the
service trade, or to setting up power plants and cement factories,
or have even gotten into agricultural development, a move that
helped state-owned coal mines avoid 100 million yuan in losses in
1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970227.0194 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China City to Bid Farewell to Poverty This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WENZHOU, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Wenzhou city in east China's
Zhejiang province, which is known for its rapid economic
development, has a plan to help its 444,000 poor people get out of
poverty by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
Although the number is down from 1995's 700,000, the local
government still needs to transform its money aid of the past to
technical aid, and from solely government-backed aid to other
channels.
</P>
<P>
The local government has set up a foundation to aid people in
mountainous areas that now has 134 million yuan. People have been
asked to join the effort, and 193 government organizations and
units in the city have established aid links with poor townships
and villages, and more than 1,300 wealthier townships and villages
hav set up sister relations with poor areas.
</P>
<P>
Natural resources will be made better use of by a number of
resource-intensive firms that have been or are being built. Last
year the city developed 10,000 ha of cash forests in mountainous
areas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
