<DOCNO> XIE19970227.0195 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southwest Chinese Region Fighting Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, February 27 (Xinhua) -- The Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region is set to allocate 120 million yuan for each of the next
four years to help its six million poor people live a better life.
</P>
<P>
The regional government will help 150,000 people living in poor
areas move to places with a better environment in that
time. Nanning, the region's capital, and Beihai, Fangchenggang,
and Qinzhou will receive 60,000 resettled people.
</P>
<P>
A large number of government-funded hydro-electric,
communications, and mining projects, and schools and hospitals
will be built in poverty-stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
One of the poorest areas in China, the autonomous region has 10
percent of the country's poverty-stricken people, and suffers from
a shortage of food, water, and an undeveloped transport system.
</P>
<P>
During the past five years, the region has terraced 53,000 ha
of mountain slopes, transformed nearly 53,000 ha of low-yield
farmland, and built 14,000 km of new highways. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
