<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northwest China Province Builds Agricultural Bases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Shaanxi
province has built ten agricultural bases as part of an
agricultural development project for better quality wheat, corn,
cotton and rice in the Guanzhong area.
</P>
<P>
Also included is an apple base in the Weibei area and a
non-staple food base in the suburbs of Xi'an.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government will put twenty percent of yearly
revenues into agriculture. Grain production in the Guanzhong area
in 1996 accounted for 70 percent of the provincial grain output
total.
</P>
<P>
The Weibei area has built 530,000 quarters for higher quality
apple production. In 1996, Shaanxi got five billion yuan (602
million US dollars) from an output of three million tons of
apples, and is the No.2 apple producer in China.
</P>
<P>
With the development of industry in the ten agricultural bases,
rural parts of Shaanxi are showing new signs of life. 
</P>
</TEXT>
