<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Limiting Textile Production Scale </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, February 27 (Xinhua) -- China plans to reduce the
production scale of its textile industry by 10 million spindles
this year, following an earlier reduction of four million spindles
across China.
</P>
<P>
The decrease was proceeded by a year-long depression in the
industry, so a package of emergency measures have been started by
the central and local government to help rescue the industry.
</P>
<P>
The industry will place emphasis in the industrial readjustment
scheme on reducing the labor force and improving efficiency, said
Wu Wenying, president of the China National Textile Council,
during an inspection tour in Shijiazhuang and Handan cities.
</P>
<P>
The readjustment will be carried out in 38 cities which have a
concentration of textile mills, this year, Wu said.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai is one of China's largest textile centers, and has
been urged to develop better technology and to produce name-brand
products. The central government is also revising policies on tax
refunds for exports and the purchase of raw materials in an effort
to help the industry out of its difficulties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
