<DOCNO> XIE19970227.0198 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Housing Fund For Beijing Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Beijing has collected 1.8
billion yuan (825 million U.S. dollars) in funds for housing for
1.9 million staff members and workers at municipal units.
</P>
<P>
According to the Beijing Housing Fund Administrative Center, by
the end of 1996, 65 percent of staff members and workers were
participating in the fund and nearly all administrative units had
a similar housing fund. A number of central government offices
have also started their own funds.
</P>
<P>
So far, 330,000 government-subsidized apartments have been
sold, with a total floor space of 20 million square meters.
</P>
<P>
Beijing began its housing reform in 1992, adopting the housing
fund system, and the administrative center now has 76
branches. This year, the housing reform will focus on
foreign-funded ventures and suburban administrative units, which
will be required to establish a similar fund.
</P>
<P>
The city has Construction Bank of China and Industrial and
Commercial Bank of China branches that deal with the housing fund.
</P>
<P>
Regulations on housing funds will be soon developed by the
State Commission for Restructuring the Economy and Housing System
Reform Leading Group of the State Council.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
