<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil Beats Poland 4-2 in Soccer Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Brazil outscored Poland
4-2 in a soccer friendly in Goiania on Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Giovanni scored two first-half goals before his Barcelona
teammate Ronaldo and Romario added a pair in the second period.
</P>
<P>
Kucharski and Citko, on a penalty kick, scored for Poland in
the final five minutes of play.
</P>
<P>
The friendly served as a warm-up for Brazil in the 1998 World
Cup wherein Brazil secured its automatic berth as reigning
champion.
</P>
<P>
While some 50,000 fans hoped both Romario, the Most Valuable
Player of the 1994 World Cup, and Ronaldo, the 1996 FIFA player of
the year, displayed their flair and forms, it was Giovanni that
stole the limelight.
</P>
<P>
In the sixth minute, Giovanni sliced apart the Poland's defense
from a pass off Ronaldo and scored the opener by tapping into the
corner.
</P>
<P>
Twenty minutes later, he made it 2-0 on a play initiated by
Romario, who returned to the team after a two-year absence.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
