<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sampras Advances in Philadelphia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 27 (Xinhua) -- World number one Pete
Sampras scored a first-round straight sets win at the ATP tennis
tournament in Philadelphia on Wednesday, keeping a winning streak
of 16 matches.
</P>
<P>
The top-seeded Sampras took 56 minutes to breeze past Marcelo
Filippini of Uruguay 6-4, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
Second seed and defending champion Jim Courier followed the
fellow American to advance after beating 89th-ranked Guillaume
Raoux of France 6-3, 7-6.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, who has twice won this tournament, captured the first
set by breaking the 79th-ranked Filippini at 30-40 on a winning
forehand approach shot, after experiencing a shaky start.
</P>
<P>
He totally dominated the second set, allowing Filippini to hold
serve only once in the second game.
</P>
<P>
Courier, a former world number one who has slipped to 18 in the
world ranking, needed one hour and 33 minutes before routing the
hard-hitting Raoux. 
</P>
</TEXT>
