<HEADLINE> Thailand's Current Account Deficit Down From 1995 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's current account
deficit last year was lower than that for 1995 in terms of
percentage of gross domestic product (GDP).
</P>
<P>
The actual current account deficit for 1996 was 7.97 percent of
GDP, lower than the 8.2 percent as projected by the Bank of
Thailand, and also lower than the 1995 level of 8.1 percent,
according to data released by the Finance Ministry available
today.
</P>
<P>
The total current account deficit for 1996 amounted to 372.6
billion baht (14.9 billion dollars), lower than the central bank's
prediction of 384 billion baht (15.36 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
Data of the Finance Ministry show that the improvement of the
current account deficit situation was in part attributable to
export growth and import decline in December last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
