<HEADLINE> Cooperation between Central America, EU Stressed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Economic cooperation between
the Central American nations and the European Union (EU) must be
further strengthened to help dispel poverty in the Central
American isthmus, a Nicaraguan communique said today.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Ministry communique quoted Nicaraguan Foreign
Minister Emilio Alvarez Montalvan, who attended the "San Jose
XIII" ministerial meeting in the Hague, Holland. He highlighted
the peace, stability and democratization in the isthmus --
favorite conditions for attracting foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, an annual ministerial forum for the Central
American countries and the EU to discuss mutual economic
cooperation, concluded today.
</P>
<P>
During his speech at the forum, Montalvan stressed the need for
the EU to allow preferential access for Central American
agricultural and industrial products.
</P>
<P>
"That would stimulate the generation of jobs, one of the
priorities of the areas and the number one priority of the
Nicaraguan government led by President Arnoldo Aleman," he added.
</P>
<P>
"The EU's cooperation has helped us immensely, not only through
support to a large number of our development projects, but also
through actions that promote our trade as well as exports," he
noted.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from all the countries of the Central American
isthmus and the EU "troika", made up of Ireland, Luxemburg and
Holland, took part in the annual ministerial forum.
</P>
<P>
After his participation in the "San Jose XIII" forum, the
Nicaraguan foreign minister will visit Germany and Spain. 
</P>
