<HEADLINE> Internet Fees Down in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, February 27 (Xinhua) -- As of March 1, Internet
charges in Thailand will be slashed by about 30 percent, it is
announced today.
</P>
<P>
For individual subscribers wishing to use only text, the new
basic entry fee is 200 baht (about 8 US dollars), compared with
the previous 800 baht (32 dollars). Monthly fees will be reduced
to 360 baht (14.40 dollars), compared with 480 (19.20 dollars).
</P>
<P>
For those who want to use graphics - for searching the World
Wide Web, for instance - the basic rate is 300 baht (12 dollars)
for the entry fee, compared to the former rate of 1,200 baht (48
dollars).
</P>
<P>
For cooperate users, the rates are more varied depending mostly
on the access speed.
</P>
<P>
The Communications Authority of Thailand has also approved
tariff cuts for overseas calls, international high-speed leased
lines and paging services.
</P>
<P>
Price reduction for overseas calls will be in the range of 6-15
percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
