furthering his private interests by interceding in favor of Export
Air de Peru. The latter has been accused of selling arms to
Ecuador during the conflicts between the Peruvian and Ecuadoran
forces several years ago.
</P>
<P>
On the second charge, Canto, who took the office of second vice
president in July 1995, could get two years in prison or two-years
community service if found guilty. 
