<HEADLINE> Italy Supports Macedonia's Bid to Join NATO, EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Italian President Oscar
Scalfaro said Wednesday that Italy supports Macedonia's bid to
join the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) and the
European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
Scalfaro, who is on an official visit to Macedonia, made the
remarks to the country's parliament, reports from the Macedonian
capital Skoplje said.
</P>
<P>
Macedonia's improvement of relations with its neighbors has
contributed to regional security, Scalfaro said.
</P>
<P>
During talks with his Macedonian counterpart President Kiro
Gligorov, Scalfaro said that the Dayton peace accord has not
brought real peace to Bosnia with the possibility of war still
existing.
</P>
<P>
The Dayton accord was reached by the Bosnian warring parties in
December, 1995, to end the three-and-half-year civil war in the
former republic of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
During Scalfaro's visit, the two countries signed agreements on
investment promotion and protection, mutual exemption of visas and
the deportation of illegal Macedonian citizens from Italy, the
reports said. 
