<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Gamini Athukorale,
general-secretary of Sri Lanka's main opposition party, the United
National Party, was shot at by unknown gunmen at Ratnapura town
Wednesday evening, but nobody was injured, police sources said
today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that Athukorale was returning after addressing
an election meeting when his vehicle was blocked by a Land Rover.
He and his security guard had alighted from the vehicle when they
were shot at.
</P>
<P>
His security guard had covered him, and villagers who were in
the vicinity had come to his rescue.
</P>
<P>
A ruling People's Alliance candidate has been identified as a
person who had got down from the Land Rover which had blocked
Athukorale's vehicle, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Political violence has been escalating throughout the country
during the run-up to the local government elections to be held on
March 21.
</P>
<P>
Police stated that since the handing in of nominations on
February 12 more than 350 incidents of violence have been reported
in the island. 
