based on a report by the Superintendent of Companies' Office on
the assets and sources of capital of companies owned by people
with previous records of drug trafficking activities.
</P>
<P>
The list of companies has been leaked to the press, even though
Superintendent Dario Laguado said the list was confidential and
would not be made public.
</P>
<P>
Laguado said many of the companies had overseas subsidiaries,
especially in the United States.
</P>
<P>
On the list are companies such as "Autopan", a chain of
bakeries belonging to the late Efrain Hernandez who was
assassinated, and Hotels and Inversismica owned by alleged drug
dealer Justo Pastor Perafan. 
