<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Thirty of the world's best
figure skaters are expected to compete in the Champions Series
Final slated for Friday in Ontario, organizers said.
</P>
<P>
With a bonus of 474,000 US dollars at stake, the elite field
includes several reigning world champions for the two-day event.
</P>
<P>
Among them were singles champions Todd Eldredge and Michelle
Kwan of the United States, and pairs title holders Marina Eltsova
and Andrei Bushkov of Russia.
</P>
