1994 and 1995, Russian Alexei Urmanov who took the 1994 Olympic
gold medal, were also among the big names for the showdown.
</P>
<P>
The top six point earners in singles, top four in pairs and top
five dance couples from a series of six international meets held
last autumn earned berths in the lucrative event.
</P>
<P>
Russia dominates the list with 10 contenders, followed by the
United States with five entries, and two each from Canada and
Ukraine. France and Germany each have one entrant.
</P>
<P>
Notably absent are Russia's world ice dance champions Oksana
Grischuk and Evgeny Platov, who won last year's Final in Paris,
and 1995 world gold medalist Chen Lu of China.
</P>
<P>
Chen and Platov were sidelined early in the season by injuries
which prevented them from qualifying. 
