<HEADLINE> Canadian Cruiser to Join Gulf Fleet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Canada is sending one of its
naval cruisers to the Gulf to join the U.S.-led allied naval
forces, Canadian Defense Minister Douglas Young said here today.
</P>
<P>
The visiting Canadian minister released the news at a press
conference before he left the United Arab Emirates (UAE). He gave
no reason for the cruiser's requirement in the force.
</P>
<P>
During his trip, Douglas discussed Canada's participation in
the third Abu Dhabi Defense Exhibition and promoted Canadian arms
sales in the Gulf country.
</P>
<P>
He said Canada's cruisers served in the U.S.-led fleets during
the Gulf War in 1991.
</P>
<P>
The minister said stability in the Gulf region is of importance
to Canada, and his country will join hands with the Gulf countries
to safeguard peace and stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
Douglas visited Kuwait before arriving in the UAE on Monday.
