<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nobel Prize Winning Chinese American Mourns Deng's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Yang Chenning, an American
physicist of Chinese origin, has sent a message of condolence to
Chinese President Jiang Zemin over the death of Chinese leader
Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
In the message, conveyed through China's Qinghua University,
Yang's Alma Mater, Yang praised Deng as one of the 20th century's
greatest leaders.
</P>
<P>
Yang recalled that he got to know Deng Xiaoping 23 years ago,
after being introduced to him by the then Chinese premier Zhou
Enlai.
</P>
<P>
During these 23 years, Deng had changed the history of the 20th
century, said Yang, who shared the Nobel Prize for Physics in 1957
with another Chinese American physicist Tsungdao Lee.
</P>
<P>
Deng emancipated the productive forces of 1.2 billion Chinese
people and created a new future for the People's Republic of
China, Yang said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
