<HEADLINE> Shanghai Microelectronics Manufacturer to Use US Gases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 27 (Xinhua) -- China's largest integrated
circuit (IC) project, the Shanghai Huahong Microelectronics Ltd.,
will pump the high-purity gases of a US air company into its IC
production line.
</P>
<P>
Huahong has recently clinched a contract with Praxair of the US
in Shanghai to get such highly purified gases as oxygen, helium,
argon, hydrogen and nitrogen.
</P>
<P>
Under the terms of the contract, the Praxair gases will be
transported to Huahong through a number of fixed pipes.
</P>
<P>
Launched in Shanghai's Pudong New Area last November, Huahong
involves a state investment of 9.6 billion yuan (about 1.2 billion
US dollars), and is expected to take the lead in China in making
0.5-micron silicon chip, one of the world's thinnest chip
standards.
</P>
<P>
The Huahong-Praxair contract is the first electronics air
project in Shanghai.  
</P>
