<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Central Agricultural Province Having More Technological Markets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Henan Province, a leading
agricultural base in China, has more than 3,000 organizations
engaged in trading of agro-techniques, accounting for 40 percent
of the total of the province's technological and trade
organizations.
</P>
<P>
These organizations do 150 million yuan in annual technological
trade business, said local officials.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, technological markets for large and medium-sized
enterprises have been established one after another, which have
helped a group of state-owned enterprises find appropriate new
technology to update their traditional industrial capabilities.
</P>
<P>
From 1990 to 1995, state-owned large and medium-sized
enterprises purchased 17,000 kinds of technology via professional
markets, with transactions totalling 1.63 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, successful technology deals had
exceeded seven billion yuan in Henan, and the number of various
kinds of technological trading organizations had also increased
from several dozen in 1985 to 7,013. Similarly, the number of
employees also went up from several hundred to 110,000.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the province was awarded the "Golden Bridge Prize" for
its efforts to expand technological markets and advance the
commercialization of scientific and technological achievements,
according to the officials.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
