HEFEI, February 27 (Xinhua) -- High-tech industrial projects
have been increasing rapidly and have become a new element in the
economic development of east China's Anhui Province.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials, Anhui's high-tech businesses
generated 7.7 billion yuan (about 928 million U.S. dollars) of
total income in 1996, up 20.4 over the previous year, and produced
989 million yuan in profits and taxes, a rise of 21.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Anhui has a strong contingent of scientific and technological
personnel. The province has worked extensively to advance the
reform of its scientific and technological system, with the
purpose of transforming many scientific achievements into actual
productivity.
</P>
<P>
And provincial authorities have offered to organize joint
projects that will combine production, training and research.
</P>
<P>
The province has established high-tech industrial development
zones in Hefei, the provincial capital, and Wuhu and Bengbu cities
since 1993, when Anhui first formally announced its plan to adopt
the strategy of relying on scientific and technological progress
for prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Since then, it has encouraged the establishment of large
high-tech industrial undertakings which enjoy privileges in
aspects including funds and taxation.
</P>
<P>
The three high-tech industrial development zones have made
headway in many ways since they were set up, local officials said.
</P>
<P>
So far, there are 255 high-tech industrial enterprises, which
have received recognition from the provincial committee of science
and technology. These firms now contribute five percent of the
province's total industrial output value each year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
