<HEADLINE> UK Asian Voters Back Labor Party </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Seventy percent of Asian voters
in Britain are likely to support the main opposition Labor Party
in Britain at the coming general election which must be held in
May, according to a MORI poll published Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The survey of 1,003 Asian voters in Britain showed that 58
percent were dissatisfied with the way the ruling Conservative
government was running the country.
</P>
<P>
Asked which party they were most inclined to support, 70
percent of them said Labor, 25 percent the Conservative and four
percent the Liberal Democrats.
</P>
<P>
After the results of the survey was published, Nirj Deva,
Britain's only Asian MP at the moment, urged the Conservative
government to "stand up and take notice", saying that "it is a
critical factor in the next election as to how these people are
going to vote."
</P>
<P>
"A difference of 200 to 300 votes this or that way will make
the shape of the next government," he added. 
</P>
