<HEADLINE> Arab Ministers of Culture Hold 10th Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, February 26 (Xinhua) -- The 10th session of Arab
Ministers of Culture opened here today with participation of
Ministers or their representatives, besides delegates of
specialized international and regional organizations.
</P>
<P>
Tunisian Prime Minister Hamid Qarawi read the opening address
of Tunisian President Zeinul Abidine Bin Ali to the two-day
session.
</P>
<P>
President Ali called in his speech for the activation of
dialogue among Arab states, and the intensification of
communication channels among Arab intellectuals. He said this
would enhance their prestige and confirm their capabilities in
shouldering their lofty mission.
</P>
<P>
The Tunisian President underscored the necessity of unifying
Arab efforts in confronting the challenges of the coming
century. He said cultural achievements of the Arab states, their
background of knowledge and their diverse potentials afforded them
the opportunity of serious intercourse with other cultures, and
established the capability of Arab culture to flourish.
</P>
<P>
The Arab Ministers of Culture will discuss the draft
resolutions and recommendations adopted by the Permanent Arab
Culture Committee at its meeting in Tunis on February 23 and 24.
</P>
<P>
The tenth session is also due to issue the Tunis Cultural
Declaration to celebrate the choice of Tunis as cultural
capital. The conference is expected to release a Statement on
Jerusalem criticizing Israel of violations against Arab and
Islamic cultural heritage and civilization in Jerusalem. 
