opposed any attempts to change the status of Jerusalem before
final status negotiations between the Palestinians and Israel will
be held.
</P>
<P>
He said Jordan viewed the Jewish settlements in East Arab
Jerusalem as "illegal and an obstacle to the Middle East peace
process."
</P>
<P>
He said that King Hussein of Jordan contacted several Arab and
world leaders in the past few days to make clear Jordan's stand
on Jerusalem and the peace process.
</P>
