<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Algeria registered a 4.3
billion U.S. dollar trade surplus in 1996, because of the rise of
crude oil prices in world oil market, increase of oil export and
cutting of imports.
</P>
<P>
Algeria registerd trade deficits of 521 million U.S. dollars in
1995 and 864 million dollars in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The Agerian government said today that the country imported 1.7
billion U.S. dollars less goods in 1996 as compared with 1995,
while its income from oil export rose to 881 million dollars in
1996 from 506 million dollars in 1995.  
