<HEADLINE> Turkey Welcomes EU Call for N.Cyprus Participation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, February 26 (Xinhua) -- The Turkish Foreign Ministry
today welcomed a proposal by leading European Union (EU)
countries calling for northern Cyprus' participation in Cyprus' EU
membership talks.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry spokesman Omer Akbel told a regular press
conference that this showed that the EU had realized that
Cyprus consisted of both southern and northern parts, describing
it as a positive step.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has been divided into two parts since 1972 when
Turkish armed forces landed on the Mediterranean island to
protect Turkish Cypriots in the weak of a Greek Cypriot coup
seeking for union with Greece.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has long opposed EU's unilateral talks with the
Cypriot government over the island state's EU membership issue.
</P>
<P>
At a European Council meeting in Brussels on Tuesday,
Germany, Britain and France said that they wanted northern
Cyprus to participate in the membership discussion of Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
However, the proposal has aroused strong opposition from the
Greek government, whose Foreign Minister Theodoros Pangalos called
it "a foolish behavior."
</P>
<P>
Pangalos said that Germany and Britain had presented a gift
to the Turkish but now they had to pay the bill, adding
that it would only block Cyprus' course towards Europe.
</P>
<P>
He warned that Greece would veto EU's enlargement program
to the east if Turkish Cypriots were allowed to be included
in the membership talks scheduled to start later this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
