<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UK World Trade Gap Narrows in December </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Britain's global trade gap
showed a surprise narrowing to 845 million pounds (1.38 billion US
dollars) in December last year after rising to a revised 1.04
billion pounds (1.7 billion US dollars) in November, official
figure shows Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Analysts had predicted December's trade gap would grow to 1.05
billion pounds (1.71 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Office for National Statistics (ONS) said world imports
rose to 14.832 billion pounds (24.18 billion US dollars) from
November's 14.791 billion pounds (24.1 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Exports rose to 13.987 billion pounds (22.8 billion US dollars)
from a revised 13.754 billion pounds (22.42 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The ONS said that the latest figures suggest that the trend in
the whole world goods deficit is narrowing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
